      • split

        public DockingRegionSplit split(DockingChild child,
                                DockingContent content,
                                boolean splitRight,
                                boolean vertical)
        Description copied from interface: DockingContainer
        Divide this container in two
        Specified by:
        split in interface DockingContainer
        Parameters:
        child - The child component which is being split. Must be a child of this container.
        content - Content to add to the newly created side of the split
        splitRight - If true, content will be placed on the right or bottom of the new split
        vertical - If true, split will divide the panel into a top and bottom. Otherwise will divide left and right.
        Returns:
        The newly created region.
